title: 1991 Ford F-250 Low Miles 2 Wheel Drive
Description:
,
A gorgeous F-250 for sale.  Low miles, new water pump, new power steering pump, cap, rotor, sparkplug wires and plugs.  Automatic transmission, 5.8L V8.  Runs like a champ; after it's been warmed up.  Comes with another set of tires and stops between gas stations is minimized due to the factory installed dual tanks.  Complete with faded paint and cow dent character.  It's in decent shape.  The drivers side arm rest has finally given way.  It has been a great truck.  I bought it a few years ago to move with.  I haven't driven it in over a year, so it's time for spring cleaning.  ,
,
What's wrong with it?,
,
It needs a passenger side valve cover gasket.  It leaks some oil from it and drips down on to the exhaust manifold.  I've thought about fixing it, but found it easier and quicker to just check the oil and roll down the window before I drove. ,
,
It starts right up and sounds good.   But I have to let it warm up a while before I can put it in gear and go.  I'm sure its something simple, but I don't have the time to figure it out.,
,
Brakes are something I would do this spring anyway.  I've never done anything with them and have towed a trailer several times over the pass.  Last time I drove it, I was thinking I should probably do them soon. ,
,

title: 2008 Subaru Impreza WRX STI - New Motor
Description:
,
We are selling this very clean 2008 STI Hatchback with 71k miles on the body and a BRAND NEW ENGINE from Subaru. ,
,
We took this vehicle in with a blown motor and decided to do an entire rebuild on the mechanical and cosmetic parts. We had the motor professionally rebuilt with receipts using OEM parts as well as many additional service items completed at the same time. ,
,
Things to note:,
Brand new all season tires,
A brand new short block from Subaru included with a 1 yr/12 month warranty,
Brand new OEM Heads and valves ,
Brand new OEM clutch kit,
Resurfaced flywheel,
Brand new step-colder iridium spark plugs,
Brand new Transmission and differential fluid change,
Brand new gaskets including head gaskets, valve seals, intake, and exhaust manifold gaskets,
Brand new OEM size turbo,
Brand new OEM oil pump, oil cooler, water pump, thermostat, and timing belt,
Brand new valve cover gasket,
Brand new Secondary Air Pump ,
New OEM Intake box and hoses,
New PCV valves,
New Starter ,
4x Rebuilt injectors,
New MAF sensor ,
Brand new shift linkage bushings,
,
,
This car has no modification except for ta tame muffler delete. No aftermarket intake or performance parts. No engine or interior modifications at all. ,
,
We just had the cosmetics gone over as well. We had the headlights resurfaced and re-sprayed with a clear coat. We just had the STI paint corrected and touched up professionally all around and it looks fantastic. All four wheels were just resurfaced, repainted and looks brand new!,
Foglights are new and we replaced them with amber bulbs. ,
,
,
Can provide anyone interested with a copy of the CarFax. The Subaru holds a CLEAN TITLE and the CarFax sports regular service history. We can provide the new owner with receipts for everything including the engine rebuild. ,
,
There is not a cleaner STI Hatchback for sale in the PNW. ,
,
We are asking $24700 for this beautiful fully sorted stock STI Hatch.

title: 2021 Chevrolet 2500 z71 Sport Edition
Description:
,
Selling my 2021 2500 Chevrolet z71 sport edition pick up truck.  ,
,
This was purchased new by me in July of 2021.  Has 10,000 miles on it and will increase as I drive it to work.,
,
Selling because I need a 3500 dually. No other reason. Truck is 100% with no issues and full factory warranty. ,
,
Firm on my price as this is my payoff amount.  For an extra amount I can transfer my extended warranty that will give you coverage to 100,000 miles. ,
,
If you’ve been looking…this truck does not exist at dealerships right now.  As pictured everything is stock.  This was a special Sport Edition Z71 long box with a black out package and painted bumpers. ,
,
Long list of factory options but include thinks like lane departure, heads up display, birds eye camera view, heated and cooling seats, Bose sound system, remote start, collision warning, hill assist, automatic rear tailgate, wireless phone charging and wireless car play. ,
,
Combined with the duramax engine and the 10 speed Alison transmission this truck is smooth shifting and fun to drive.    ,
,

title: Ford Expedition 1997 Sport utility truck/suv
Description:
,
So I'll start with the bad.,
,
It is a missing lug on the front left and the tires could be better and then Clean it!!,
,
,
,
The drivers window needs the regulator installed and the new part in ready to be installed.   For those that don't know that means some time working on the install for that window assembly .,
,
  The new part comes with the deal.,
,
  It Didn't have a muffler when I bought it and still doesn't  however it's  not loud at all. ,
,
 It        "needed"     brakes on the front end to avoid disaster :-)   That work is done?!!,
,
They have maybe 500 miles on them with absolutely no problem.,
,
Stereo works but the speaker that's in the driver side door isn't a fit. AC was overhauled mid summer for a boat trip to the Gorge for a 3 day run and it towed fabulously.,
,
The toe was for a 22 foot runabout ski boat heavily loaded for fun and it went perfect coming and going from Snoqualmie to Quincy and back and the trailer lights functioned perfectly.,
,
 This is in Snoqualmie and the location for the paperwork is in the Safeway parking lot in North bend the ladies are fabulous at expediting and helping!,
,
If I find any time I'll keep cleaning and the like but that's not likely.

title: Food Truck for sale
Description:
,
Hello.  The food truck is L&I approved and is ready to be put into action by the new owner immediately (assuming you have the necessary health permits, business licenses, etc.).,
,
-- Please note - The outside wrap has been removed because the truck is for sale, but the business is not part of the sale, so the outside of the truck is plain white,
-- 1998 Chevy P30,
-- New engine installed summer, 2021,
-- New radiator installed summer, 2021,
-- New generator installed fall, 2020,
-- Generator is a built-in Cummins Onan 6.5HGJAE-2145M,
-- Built-in 40-gallon propane tank,
-- Truck also has a plug-in option,
-- Interior was professionally designed & built (i.e. stainless-steel shelves, sinks, plumbing, electric, etc.),
-- 48" Vulcan heavy duty gas griddle,
-- 48" Delfield undercounter refrigerator with open "salad top" that can hold 12 1/6 size pans,
-- 48" Delfield undercounter refrigerator flat-top,
-- Brand new 15# counter-top fryer - installed October, 2021,
-- Vulcan 1024W wall-mounted cheesemelter,
-- 3 compartment sink plus handwashing sink,
-- 35-gallon fresh water tank, 42-gallon gray water tank,
-- Lots of built-in stainless-steel shelves,
-- Jumpseat installed in truck cab so you can take two passengers plus driver,
-- Fire suppression system, including two fire extinguishers (K class and regular),
-- Lots of extras included with sale - traffic cones, leveling blocks, wheel chocks, propane/gas detector, etc.

title: 2005 Cadillac CTS V OBO
Description:
,
Brand new remanufactured engine, comes with 3 year/100k warranty. The warranty is transferable and covers parts and labor for another engine if needed, no questions asked. The original 5.7L LS6 engine was sent down to Texas to be remanufactured from the block out. You can take the car into any shop in the area that works with the engine maker (jasper engines) to get any kind of engine maintenance done including a new engine for free. I worked with "Eastside Automotive" on 85th st in kirkland for the engine install, I'd recommend bringing it to them if any issues arise since they are familiar. I replaced the engine with the sole intent of selling the vehicle. I've put about 100 miles on the car since the engine was installed. It is ridiculously fast, super fun to drive. This engine work cost 12,000$.,
The car also has a brand new upgraded LS7 clutch with less than 1000 miles on it. The clutch is about 70lbs lighter than the stock clutch, it performs great. I got the clutch installed at the Bellevue cadillac dealership. The new clutch with a couple extra items was about 4,000$.,
Got a new starter about 1500 miles ago. Installed by Bellevue cadillac. New starter was about 1600$ with an engine tune up. ,
Rear seals on the differential replaced about 1200 miles ago.,
I've got all the receipts and warranty info for the above work. I also have 20,000$ of service records from the previous owner (2008-2020), all work done by Bellevue Cadillac. ,
I'm the third owner of this vehicle.,
This vehicle runs like it has 0 miles on it. ,
I'm selling this vehicle because I'd like to purchase a home soon. ,
,
Pros:,
New engine w/ warranty,
New upgraded clutch,
Interior in good condition,
New starter,
New rear differential seals,
Exterior in good condition,
5% tint on all windows except windshield (limo tint),
400hp,
Bose sound system sounds great,
Every function of this vehicle is in working order,
,
Cons:,
Could use a new windshield,
,

title: 2008 Ford F-150 4WD Lariat SuperCrew
Description:
,
This has been a great truck and drives extremely smooth.  I have all of the available maintenance/repair records since 2012.  There were no major repairs besides expected belt/spark plugs every few years.  A few years ago I upgraded the wheels to the matte black Fuel off-road wheels as well as new tires recently (Micheline LTX A/T 2; with less than 15K miles on them. They have a 60K warranty through Costco). I also recently added the Tonneau truck bed cover, which is a great amenity, especially to keep the rain out in the PNW! I added auto-start to the vehicle which is also a great feature for cold rainy days and even those snow days! I was one of the only folks on the road driving comfortably in the recent snow! You’ve got to love the 4WD.  I am the second owner (only 2 owners total) but this truck has been well maintained throughout its existence.,
,
I am deciding to sell this truck since my wife recently bought a new vehicle for our family, a Subaru ascent. We now have 3 vehicles and we want to reduce our car inventory so we can fit all vehicles in our driveway/garage.  It rides much better than my wife’s new car to be honest! It's not easy for me to let this great truck go! I hope that we can find a prospective owner that will take great care of it.,
,
Honest Disclaimer: ,
-There are 2 locations where the leather is beginning to come apart at the seams (back right and driver seat).  I use the seat covers once I noticed this to help protect them.,
-There is a small dent on the rear tailgate (not noticeable in my opinion),
-There are a few scratches on the roof of the car (not visible unless you stand on the truck bed),

title: 2005 Ford F-150
Description:
,
Selling my 2005 F150 with the offroad FX4 package. I am the 2nd owner and have owned the truck for the last 6+ years. Reason for selling is because I am moving and no longer need the vehicle. Truck runs/drives well and is in good condition. Mainly used for 5 mile daily commute and mountaineering trips on the weekend.,
,
Highlights,
- 4 wheel high/low work as expected,
- brake pads have plenty of life left in them and rotors are in great condition,
- oil changed every 4500 miles, fuel filter every year,
- hard top cover for truck bed included,
- aux port for phones installed and easy to use,
,
Known issues:,
- after about approximately 30-60 min of driving, the overdrive light will begin to blink and a "Trans Fault" message will appear on the info screen. This has been occurring for over a year and has never resulted in any driving degradation,
- After the truck has sat for several hours and the weather is cold (normal morning startup conditions), initially shifting from park to drive/1st gear occasionally fails and the truck will go into limp mode. Once the truck is in first, I have not experienced any other issues. This has been occurring for a month.,
- black plastic on radio buttons/transmission shifter have deteriorated,
- window washer fluid spray mechanisms do not work,

title: 1987 Porsche 944 Base - bring a trailer
Description:
,
I have a 1987 Porsche 944 in Guards Red for sale.  ,
,
I've owned the car for a little over two years now, purchased in November 2019.  Odometer was broken upon me purchasing it.  Odometer says 196k miles.  I wouldn't have guessed based on how it drives.  ,
,
I've done a ton of work on this car during covid.  Helped keep me busy during lockdown, and genuinely enjoy driving/wrench on this vehicle.  New brakes all around, new radiator, new thermostat, spark plugs, distributor, cap, spark wires, throttle cam, fuel pump, fuel filter, Porsche 944 turbo rear sway bar, RARE late offset 16inch Porsche 944 phone dial wheels and new tires that only have at most 5k miles, only944 LED front headlights, and lots of other little things along the way. ,
,
I took fantastic care of this thing, with oil changes every 3 months regardless of mileage.  I frequently would take this car for long spirited drives all over western Washington.  It drove and handled like a dream.  ,
,
Car was stolen from my home in Queen Anne a month ago.  Seattle police recovered it 5 days after it was stolen. ,
,
The thrives took a sawzall to the ignition lock cylinder and sawed straight through the lock cylinder to turn on the car and drive away.  Besides the fact it will need a new ignition cylinder, the only other damage to the car is some curb rash on one of the wheels (in the pics), and one of the front bumper struts will need to be replaced (in the pics).  The car has NOT been started in about 30 days.  ,
,
Thieves have stolen 2 other cars from my street in the last 30 days since my car was stolen.  Therefore, it's unfortunately not in my best interest to fix it and keep it.  It's just gonna be a sitting duck.  ,
,
I'm not in a rush to sell it, it's happily parked in a safe place for now.  It's a great car, and ready for the next owner to bring it back to it's normal operating condition or maybe take advantage of the situation and make it into an awesome track car.  ,
,
I disassembled the steering wheel/ignition components to see if I could do it myself.  I have all the pieces, but it requires either a tap/die to fully get the ignition lock cylinder off, or you could just take a sawzall and break the rest of it off considering the lock cylinder is already broken.  Either way, I opted not to screw with it and the next owner can make that decision.  A new lock cylinder can be found for like $100-200 online.  ,
,
It's a 35 year old car.  It is not perfect but I daily drove it for years with no issues, and never left me stranded.  Gets compliments everywhere I go. The car does have some paint fade on the roof and driver's door.  I used to keep it waxed and you'd never know.  The interior is alright, not fantastic but cleans up well.  The seats have some splits in the them.  ,
,
$5,000 cash takes it.  I will not show this car unless you have cash in hand.  ,
,
I'm very disappointed to sell this car, lots of fantastic memories driving it and climbing underneath on sunny afternoons to do wrenching.  I have nowhere safe to keep it long-term, my quiet little street in Queen Anne just isn't safe anymore and I'd rather see it go to someone else who can take care of it and have fun with it.  ,
,
I do not need help selling this car.  If the ad is up, it's still for sale.,
,
Comes with tons of other parts, and things that I never got around to doing.  Also includes the original 15 inch phone dials that were on the car when I bought it.

title: Mercury Milan (Ford Fusion)  LOW MILES! 109K

,
Very nice luxury sedan! This is the upscale model of the Ford Fusion and similar to the Lincoln MKZ!    Top of the line with lots of whistles and bells! ,
  Heated Leather Seats, BLUETOOTH PHONE, Moon roof, Microsoft Sync voice-activated audio system, ( allows the driver hands-free communication when using a cell phone, selecting music from an external MP3/iPod-like device or surfing satellite radio.! ) keyless entry, Upgraded sound system, steering controls,  ,

,

"Milan is impressively quiet. The use of satin aluminum finishes and high-quality materials is meant to extend the appeal of the Milan’s body into its five-passenger cockpit. Roomy and open-feeling up front, the Milan offers plenty of head and elbow space for the driver and front passenger. . A 60/40 split-folding rear seat is standard. The extended back doors make entry easier for taller passengers.",
,
Standard Features,
The 2008 Mercury Milan comes nicely equipped and includes front-seat side-impact airbags, side-curtain airbags, a tilt/telescoping steering wheel with redundant audio controls, remote keyless keypad entry, air conditioning, speed control, a Securilock passive anti-theft system, power heated mirrors, anti-lock brakes (ABS) and power windows and locks. title: 1972 Chevelle Gen V/6sp auto custom
Description:
,
1972 Chevelle looking for its forever home. It’s a complete frame off restoration. The car was stripped completely and put on my rotisserie and repaired while the frame and suspension pieces went off to the sand blaster and was powder coated black. When the chassis came back from the powder coater, it received all new bushings, bearings, brakes and HD sway bars. It has front and rear power disk brakes. The 10-bolt rear diff was also powder coated black and now holds a limited slip and 3:73 ring and pinon. I have a 12-bolt diff housing that you’re welcome to if you want it with the car. I had it powder coated to match the chassis.,
Under the hood is a 2017 Silverado Gen 5 5.3 L83 V8. It’s one of the new style GM direct Injected V8 engines. It has a corvette intake manifold to keep the height down and fit under the hood. Stock exhaust manifolds feed dual exhaust.,
I purchased the engine/trans combo from Engine Swap Supply, in Houston Texas. I was told this engine/trans have approx. 10k miles on it when it was removed from a 2017 2wd Silverado. No smoke, no leaks. Runs like a champ!!,
Behind the engine is a six-speed automatic transmission, the 6L80E. Runs and shifts great. I added a new style GM shifter.,
This car has Vintage Air a/c, power steering, all four windows are power up/down, stock interior with all new seats, dash pad, dash assembly, knobs, door panels, and carpet. Before installing the interior, I lined the entire inside of the car with Dynamat Extreme. Floor, sides, doors, roof, you name it, it’s probably covered in Dynamat.,
Retrosound stereo system with custom kick panel speakers, and a custom-built center console for the new style Camaro shifter round out the interior. Monitoring the engine, is a set of Dakota Digital gauges. They interface directly with the OBDII of the engine and can display almost anything you’d like. I have them set to show multiple options, but you can choose almost anything you’d like to monitor on the engine. They even show 0-60 times and ¼ mile times!,
I finished this beautiful car up a few weeks back and have been driving it back and forth to work and around town. So far, I’ve put 250 miles on the odometer with no issues whatsoever. I plan to keep driving it every day till it sells. Only time I won’t be driving it is when the roads freeze up. It’s a lot of fun to drive! I’ve got a full shop of other projects and am looking to sell it to make some room to try to finish them up. Feel free to email/call me with any questions. I also have quite a few pics of the process. Let me know if you’d like to see something specific. Thanks for looking!!

The 1986 Jeep CJ7 is the last model of the 1976-through-1986 CJ7 series production run. It's an offspring of the venerable 1954-to-1984 CJ5 series, but it had a longer wheelbase and upgraded mechanical features. I am 6'-6" inches tall and am comfortable driving my Jeep.,
,

126K Original Miles,

5 Speed Manual Transmission,
Hard Top,
Spare Tire Carrier (w/Spare Tire),

33x12.50R15LT Goodyear Wrangler (Duratrac) Tires on Stock Steel Jeep Rims,
Factory Full Instrumentation Dashboard with Speedometer, Warning Lamps, Tachometer, and Lever Controlled Heat/Air Circulation Vents,
Factory Bucket Seats (Front),
Factory Bench Seat (Rear),
Factory Center Console,

Factory Skid Plate,
,

,

,

,
Call or Text Carlos  ,
. Texting works best for me. Please be patient for my reply.  ,
,
Thank you.,

title: Extremely RARE 2008 Roush 427R TRAK PAK Mustang #11 of 100
Description:
,
!).   Jack Roush has achieved tremendous success in various forms of motorsports and equally been successful in aftermarket parts and tuning.   In 2008 Roush offered a unique limited-edition package for the new Ford Mustang GT’s.   For one year only, Roush built just 100 special production 427R Trak Pak Mustangs.   The vehicle we have for is #11 of the 100 units produced.  It is also 1 of 1 in that no other Trak Pak Mustangs were produced with the unique Blue with Red highlight combination.  The car is in excellent condition and shows 81K miles.   The bad news is that the car does have a branded title, however, don’t be concerned.   The car was involved in a minor debris impact along the front lower air dam (photos available).   Damage was minor (intercooler, bumper cover, lower radiator support, however it unfortunately did trigger the driver’s airbag.   No structural or other mechanical damage was done from the otherwise minor incident.   Apparently, due to the airbag deployment the insurance company chose to not repair it and that’s how we acquired the car.   The car was professionally repaired with factory Ford and Roush parts (including all airbag and related safety components) and subsequently fully inspected by the Washington State Patrol.   The car looks and drives amazing and is in very solid mechanical condition.   Since its repair it’s only been used occasionally and displayed in local car shows.,
Roush’s Trak Pak Mustangs were intended to be driven to the racetrack for a day of fun yet be comfortably and reliably driven back home.   #11 was fully optioned (build sheet attached).  Included with the car are instructions tuning its unique suspension as well as other articles, reviews, and information on the TRAK PAK cars.   This car will be a great addition to any Mustang car enthusiast’s collection or for one looking for an affordable but reliable track car.,

title: Classic 1975 Mercedes Benz 450SL
Description:
,
Mercedes SL’s are increasingly being sought after and the values continue to rise.  This is a example of the classic pagoda era SL’s.   It has classic Mercedes silver exterior paint with the blue interior.  It has both a hard top and the soft top.  The car is powered by the 4.5L Mercedes V8 with an automatic transmission.  This is not a show car but a decent ”driver quality” car.   The silver paint is fresh but not to a concours level.   The car runs down the road smoothly and comfortably with that expected solid Mercedes feeling.   The odometer shows 53,000 miles, however we are not sure of actual miles as the odometer doesn’t appear to consistently rotate as it should even though the speedometer works just fine.    The car had a WSP inspection after we acquired it.  The tan soft top cloth isn’t perfect and has some wear areas but is usable.  The electric windows work but the edge of one of the side windows shows some minor chips.  Engine runs and fires up right away but may benefit from a fresh tune up and sounds like it might have a small exhaust manifold leak on the passenger side.  Transmission shifts and operates smoothly.  The original radio is still installed and works.    Enjoy it as it is or put a little more TLC into it and have an even nicer car.     Prices continue to climb on these.  Low NADA classic car retail is now over $13K and Average value is over $25K.   This classic Mercedes roadster can be yours $8500.,
